ygData.messageBody:
I think I can answer some of this, and am surprised you didn't spot it too
with all the time you spend there. The white critters are frogloks I
believe. The one with the glowing eyes is perhaps the first undead froglok?
Their eyes are a glowing yellow as I recall. Did they have a war with the
kobolds perhaps?

Kit

From: Ryan Honeyman [mailto:honeyman@...]

Subject: Re: [eqbards] Norrathian Lore: Nagafen's Lair


From: Ryan Honeyman <honeyman@...>

#13, this picture scares me the most.

I suppose first of all you have to identify the elements in the
paintings. There are white creatures (small), there are white
creatures (bigger, but are they the same thing?), there are brown
things (small, usually laying down) and brown creatures that are
bigger possibly the same thing but standing up. Then there is this
doglike creature, much bigger than the rest.

Some figures are laying down (as if dead), some have weapons,
some are dancing, some are running, some are chasing others
while others are being chased.

Back to #13, lots of dead? brown creatures, one of them has
yellow glowing eyes, while the small white creatures appear
to be dancing? around it? Truly weird.

Harmonic.
